caption: Picked up nigiri last minute. Good food. Great service.

Love this little ramen shop. Sister resultant to the Ten Ichi mart next door. Food is authentic and priced well. They have a great selection for grab n go meals too. Looking forward to the quarantine ending so we can experience this place in full. It has a nice patio outback with draft beer and heat lamps. Great for a quick meal with outdoor seating that puts the customers safety first.
Got the ramen to go and it was gorgeous! We'll be back as the whole family was jealous of my soup.

Nice place, easy to order and you can sit outback and eat, they have heat lamps but it wasn't on when we got there. We took the $14 beef udon and the $14 beef ramen. I liked the beef ramen but the beef udon wasn't that good. The restroom was very clean. They don't take discover anymore, but other cards.
One of the best ramen shops I been to , and I been to ipputo , hinamaru and ichiran ...

Love their veggie ramen with tofu. Super filling and tasty. I‘ve also had their vegetable tempura which is sweet potatoes and it’s one of my favorite. Great service and a cute little outdoor in the backyard.

The best miso ramen I have ever had. They also get points for great chashu.  I could order this ramen every night in winter. Highly recommend.  Service is excellent.  They also have a full japanese grocer next door so you know  they know what they are doing.

This ramen restaurant is amazing and also, the next-door Japanese supermarket is very good and cheap! Ramen soup is authentic and strong. Noodles are chewy and won't taste as bad as ordinary ramen houses. In addition, poke bowls are also highly recommended for trial. During the COVID-19, its backyard is open with a good environment and flower fragrance! I highly recommend coming over for lunch and sunbathing!
The backyard is so amazing. Ramen tastes good!

I have been to this place a lot but today was the worst experience ever. I was picking up two orders of ramen, and they told me it would be 10-15 mins wait. After 30 mins my order came out wrong so I had to wait another 10 mins. Then I got home and started to eat it and found a bug in my ramen. Never coming here again!

Food was delicious! Service was horrible! We went on a Friday night, ordered our food To - Go and the server said 15mins. After about 30mins we realized that the server wasn't efficient and left our to - go order sitting on the counter along with 5 other orders. Everyone standing outside was angry that the server was extremely slow and not prepared to handle a Friday night rush. If she had hustle in her step and a bit of focus, all can be forgiven. However after waiting 45 - minutes for our food as it sat on the counter and standing outside amongst other angry hungry people was not cool. I understand everyone is under staffed or cutting back staff due to Covid, however this place was a mess and should have at least another server to handle the load.  But the food delicious. Just don't go on a Friday night and be prepared to wait a while for your food and it may not be hot when you get it.  Everyone was cursing the server under their breath. Tragic.

The service was decent the appetizers are also however I was very disappointed with the  Pork Ramen.... the broth was not to my liking sweet for some reason ..the noodle had a waxy texture and was a bit undercooked...I would much recommend Zaya Ramen for more flavorful taste!

Worst ramen I’ve had in Brooklyn but the appetizers were pretty good and the service was friendly. Ordered the beef ramen but for whatever reason it was almost sweet and lacked any deep flavor for being beef bone broth. Edamame was good and  the chicken wings were tasty but could have been tossed in the sauce instead of it just being layed on top. They could definitely added more octopus to their takoyaki even though it usually only has a small piece of leg you would think they sliced it with a mandolin. I hope this was a bad day for them since I went based on the reviews but didn’t receive any of the quality I was looking for. Go to Zaya Ramen if you want something worth it.

Their food is sooo good. Very fresh, lots of flavor. I order the lunch special which was veggie ramen and veggie bun and sweet potato rolls. Their tofu is seasoned very well and has flavor. My husband order chicken ramen and enjoyed it. Sweet potato rolls are nice and crunchy. I would def. go back.
Did not disappoint. The Ten Ichi ramen broth was incredibly savory and not too heavy or salty and with the noodles being just the right amount of chewiness.
Very hygenic and prompt service! The backyard has socially-distanced tables and chairs

This place have good backyard patio for dining. The place is nice and well-lit. I ordered the miso ramen that comes with chasu pork, ground pork and vegetables which was good. What surprised me the most was actually their takoyaki, it came out pretty good

Tonkatsu Ramen here? So so so so so good. It is a miso Pork version. Sublime and punchy. Chasu and ground pork and mushrooms in the base. YES!!! Not too salty. Ordered for way less scallions. Added egg. New favorite.
Amazing food
Great food That's all there is to it
Wow. Really really good. We randomly walked by and found this little gem. We tried different kinds of ramen, the buns and the wings. Everything is absolutely amazing!

I finally found a ramen place that I love in Brooklyn. The soup base is not overly rich which is my preference. They also make their own noodles! Their appetizers are equally delicious too. We are definitely come back next time when we are craved for Ramens.
I adore this venue very much. theres a happy atmosphere. The kitcen is wonderful. the service is efficient and the team is professional. The price is satisfactory. very much recommend.
The staff was very nice, the hand towels were amazing, but the food was just ok.
Great lunch time ramen spot. Quick and pleasant service.
Love this food. Discovered is place in Park Slope and I love it. I'm glad that it's right in my neighborhood now so I can eat it frequently.
Tasty Ramen. Almost as good as in Japan.
Really good ramen . Nice staff . The broth is very good and chicken or beef one of you don't eat pork
Mmm, good pork buns.
Great atmosphere and delicious ramen.
Love the vegan ramen
Service was nice and so was the food.
Delicious, creamy ramen in beef broth. I loved the salmon ramen. Quick service.
I enjoyed their tempura and their fried chicken more than their ramen!
The ramen was amazing, the broth was sooo rich!!!

Vegetables with a strong flavor (I didn't know what it was) accented and enriched the taste.  (Original) 正直、期待していなかったところもあるのですが、想像以上においしかったです。風味が強めの野菜(何かはわかりませんでした)がアクセントになって、味を豊かにしてくれました。
The restaurant is awesome and spacious, the meals was delightful and the prices were very economical. rapidly, effective service and very welcoming waiters. Highly recommended.

Ten Ichi. The place was so small I thought it would be better served to be named Ten Inches, as in Ten square Inches of space. It's not designed for well-fed, grown men like me. But that was the only draw back. The decor was simple yet elegant. I liked the little Mason jar with the LED lights in it turned upside down. Very innovative, very Brooklyn. Our service was excellent, prompt and courteous. The place was packed (a good sign) and people were walking in still trying to carve out their own inch, so prompt service that you can eat and go is a must at this obviously popular restaurant. We ordered the duck bun to start and a beef ramen for me and a pork ramen for my Jewish friend. Don't ask. In a word...delicious. Very tender and flavorful pieces of meat, veggies and al dente noodles all having a ball swimming in a deliciously tasty and balanced broth. So satisfying that we couldn't waste spoonful of deliciousness with conversation. We were only left with Mmm's, and Ohh's when we found another interesting spoonful. Besides we had to finish so that the others waiting outside could get their turn. I'll be back, with my other big friends.
Tried here last week, the broth was flavorless , chashu was too oily , have better ramen place in Brooklyn.
Deeeelicious. Lunch special on weekends is a pretty good deal!!!
Great lunch special!

Rich, flavorful broth; luscious homemade noodles; melt-in-your-mouth chashu; tasty additions. Spinach salad appetizer is delicious, and probably the best-looking salad you’ll ever get for $7. Incredibly friendly and fast service.
Fantastic food, friendly staff, great location.

Really good, I enjoyed the ramen a lot, if you want ramen go here? There was a man- what a man. Had a mustache which I liked and an earring that my girlfriend liked. Charismatic and made the eating experience all the better. Will come back!
The wings and ramen are so good. I always get the beef rayu ramen. Its a solid choice
I got the miso pork ramen. It was delicious. Staff was incredibly nice.

Ten Ichi noodle is good. Chicken wings are not marinated, don’t like it. Pork Gyoza is edible. Buta bun is also edible. If you need a quick fix of Ramon noodle, you can come here. Otherwise, there are better places.
Good food, good atmosphere, I’ll come again.

On the one hand, this is just a local ramen joint. This is reflected in the … easy?... pace of service. As I put it to my wife, borrowing a mode of analysis from my engineer son, "They appear to be cooking things serially rather than in parallel." On the other hand, the staff is very pleasant, and, most importantly, the ramen is really good. I particularly like the sesame broth-based ramen, including the chashu pork ramen.  If you are on Smith Street, or even nearby, be sure to give it a try.
Love it.
Great homemade ramen! They even offer cold ramen for summer;) Poke bowl toppings are very fresh.

A wonderful atmosphere that's perfect for a casual lunch or an evening date with a partner this local ramen shop offers a seasonal menu and lunch combo. Modest prices, adequate sizes and pleasant atmosphere had this spot in my good books before I took that first bite. I found the broth flavorful and nuanced, each sip exploded on my tongue, additionally the chicken was well seasoned and my egg was perfect. For just under 20 bucks you can grab a bowl of ramen (cold noodles for those warmer days) an appetizer and a drink. If I'm ever in the area again for work I know where to go for a great meal that won't destroy my wallet.

The food is OK at best. I went with my family(3 adults 1 teen and 2 kids. We were forced to pay 20% tip as it was added to our bill because of 6 or more people in the group (apparently it sead that somewhere in the menu). Everyone had one bowl of ramen with 1 order of gyoza (pot stickers) to share. Our bill was $170! Nice staff but wow what a price for average food. I will never go back.
Their Ten Ichi ramen was surprisingly excellent. They have a cold ramen dish similar to Tsukemen. Docked one star because the sides (gyoza and pork bun) were lackluster.
The ten ichi ramen was excellent. Lovely seating area and the employees were very helpful

Not bad
Good taste. Tiny portion
They put the soup chicken in the freezer for long day more the owner weing no like pay always said no busy no money

We enjoyed our ramen. It's nice to finally have some good ramen on Smith Street! We had the vegetarian ramen and the ten ichi classic ramen. We also had the duck bun and the pork belly bun. Both were quite delicious. We're looking forward to coming back and trying the tempura and the poke.
Good pork broth
Our go-to Ramen place. Way better than you might think! The broth is good and clean, the noodles are yummy. Great neighborhood staple!
Got some takeout, little expensive bit quick.and it was good.

OMG fantastic. Wonderful tempura appetizer of shrimp and shishito pepper, then vegetarian ramen. The broth was super flavorful, the noodles were fresh, and I was stuffed at the end of the meal. Service was friendly, helpful, and fast. Definitely earned my repeat business!

Had a ramen yesterday, the broth was so bland and oily, noodles were still hard, waitresses were so rude, and it took 10 minutes to come back and provide me with the check. Had the nerve to tell me I MUST tip them after such horrible service though there was nothing on my receipt stating so. NEVER coming here again.
Very tasty ramen
The ramen is legit.

I don't give 5 star reviews often but I came in for takeout and came home to 2 delicious bowls of ramen. Very tasty egg cooked perfectly and the soups we're both excellent! I plan on returning more often especially with the very fair price they charge. $13 a bowl better than $16-20 elsewhere in the area. Highly recommended..  PS this is 5 star compared to other NYC ramen, can't compare this to ramen in Japan or some places like Mu Ramen in LIC is fantastic as well but much much pricier, for $12/13 a bowl here it hits the spot!  Additional, finally ate here dine in and the service was excellent! They filled water glasses without asking and gave extra napkins without asking either. Those little attentive things really make a difference sometimes.
Great broth, portions were a little small but quality was excellent!
Honestly? Ramen is super disappointing. Flavorless toppings and the broth lacks any depth and is strangely... Not salty? Gyoza we're good though.
Very tasty ramen. Clean bathrooms. Good service.

(Translated by Google) It is good inside. Tenichi ramen is salmon and pork bone. The soup feels like one more thing is missing, but I think it's delicious enough. Especially noodles are good. It is extra-fine noodle like Hakata ramen. It was exciting to eat this hard thin noodles overseas. Dumplings are delicious! It was written as homemade, but it is delicious. Pork bang is also delicious horned GOOD! It is a good customer service and I would like to go there again.  (Original) 中々良いです。天一ラーメンは🍜、豚骨です。スープは、もう一つ何かが足りないな〜って感じですが、十分美味しいと思います。 特に、麺は良いですね。博多ラーメンの様に極細麺です。海外でこの硬めの細麺が食べれるのは感激しました。 餃子は🥟、はっきり言って美味い！ 自家製と書いていましたが、美味いです。 豚バンも、角煮が美味しくGOOD！ 接客も良く、また食べに行きたいお店です。

This is an Asian comment…food are little bit under ordinary, even in American level of ramen. And the portion are small. Service is mixed, the servers are very polite but the serving was very slow last time. Though servers tried hard to please us
Great food, nice servers, and a nice atmosphere inside and out, on a street full of fun stuff to do! Keep up the good work, Ten Ichi team!
It’s ok. As a Japanese I could be pickier with ramen than other people. Gyoza and takoyaki were great though.
Great lunch specials.
All other ramen restaurants take note: this is what Pork Chashu needs to be. Please. Just... I can't even. I love you Ten Ichi <3

Second time here, and again everything was delicious. Since coming here last time I had a couple other very highly reviewed ramens and they were no where near as good. I don’t normally review unless a place makes me sick or is extraordinary. Enjoy.

I really hope the manager will read my comment... I came on last Saturday night and the food was good BUT the service, I have never seen that ! I'm working in the restaurant industry and I don't like to leave a comment like that since I know how rude some customers are. Requesting the payment while we're still eating, plus asking more tips since we were unhappy of the service, it's an unacceptable behavior. Being kick out of the restaurant since the employee want to finish his shift and clean under our table, it's unbelievable ! Finally we decided to leave the restaurant without finishing our meal and the server threw the coins at us and quickly closed the restaurant's door behind him !  In order to respect this industry, please change your servers because it will take you to bankrupt.
Good food, nice servers, good price. Just need to get the draft Sapporo going. ;)
Great,Food, Great seating, Great restaurant!
Classic Japanese kitchen with a couple modern touches.

Wow I was not aware they have a backyard. Easily a $16 dinner for a bowl of noodle. Hmm that's for you to judge if it's expensive or now. For me, it's cheaper than a $20 cocktail and definitely a lot more art and work.  How does it taste? I love the broth. I can taste the time and effort to make that thick broth. If you order a spicy noodle, you ruin the taste. I love spicy but not really in ramen. It's like putting a screen protector on an iPhone screen. What a waste. Anyway, i suggest the egg. If not in your noodle selection, you can ask to a dd it for some $$ of course.  Ramen is really good. Here and also for your belly. Portion is a bit enough? I will always complain about portion being small thou. It's enough to make you feel happy but not totally full.  I was here at 7:30pm on a weekday and it's totally empty or maybe another table leaving. Ever since that other ramen place  closed 6 blocks away by Hoyt, this is probably the only one left in the area or at least one of the best. I wouldn't come often because I don't spend $16 on casual dinner everyday. I am a make my own dinner or go for the $5 gyro kind of person. In the end, I think you should try this place. It's delicious.
A wonderful new place, great tasting food. The server was very helpful explaining the menu. Will return vey soon.
